  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add diced beef and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove beef and set aside.",
    "In the same pot, sauté onions, carrots, celery, and garlic until softened, about 7 minutes.",
    "Stir in tomato paste and cook for 2 minutes to caramelize.",
    "Return beef to pot, pour in beef broth, add lemon juice, pickled cucumber, and salt.",
    "Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 45 minutes until beef is tender.",
    "Stir in chopped dill, season to taste with salt if needed.",
    "Ladle stew into bowls, garnish with a drizzle of lemon juice if desired.",
    "Serve hot with crusty bread or over boiled potatoes."
  ],
